  <h2 class="recipe-headings" id="pancakes">Vegan Pancakes</h2>
  <p> This batter will make <em>soft pancakes</em> with a <em>thin, cripsy crust.</em>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Prep Time</th>
          <th>Total Time</th>
          <th>Servings</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>15 Minutes</td>
          <td>45 Minutes</td>
          <td>3-4 People</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <table> <br>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Quantity</th>
          <th>Ingredient</th>
          <th>Quantity</th>
          <th>Ingredient</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td id="ingredientsize">1 1/4 Cup</td>
          <td>Flour</td>
          <td id="ingredientsize">1/2 Teas</td>
          <td>Salt</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td id="ingredientsize">2 Tables</td>
          <td>Sugar</td>
          <td id="ingredientsize">2 Teas</td>
          <td>Baking Powder</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td id="ingredientsize">1 1/4 Cup</td>
          <td>Water</td>
          <td id="ingredientsize">1 Tables</td>
          <td>Oil</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>
      <strong>Step 1:</strong> Sift and & Combine Dry Ingredients in a mixing bowl. Start preheating skillet on low heat with a bit of oil on it. <br>
      <strong>Step 2:</strong> Add wet ingredients and use a whisk to gently mix ingredients together. DO NOT OVERMIX. Batter will small have lumps, these will cook out. <br>
      <strong>Step 3:</strong>Use a 1/4 cup to pour out pancakes on the preheated skillet. Adjust tempurature. For best results do not compress pancakes between flips, this makes dense instead of fluffy.
    </p>

    <em>Source: <a href="file:///C:/Users/Tim/Google%20Drive/Kitchen/Vegan%20Pancakes%20-%20Printer%20Friendly%20-%20Allrecipes.com.html">AllRecipes.com</a></em>
  </p>

